Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve @lime{1}. Trim root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves.

Pat @ground beef{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Halve any larger pieces of beef if necessary.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

In the last ~{30%seconds} of cooking, add scallion whites; stir to combine.

== Sesame Slaw ==

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and juice from lime. Season with salt and pepper. Microwave until cabbage is slightly softened, ~{30-60%seconds}. (You'll finish the slaw later.)

== Sauce ==

Reduce heat under pan with beef to medium low. Stir in @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @gochujang{1/2%oz}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring frequently, until sauce has thickened and beef is coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Swap in beef for chicken. Cook beef, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, 4-6 minutes.

== Assembly ==

Add @sesame dressing{1.5%oz} and half the @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} (save the rest for serving) to bowl with cabbage and carrot mixture. Toss to combine.

Divide lettuce leaves between plates; fill with sesame slaw. Top with beef and any remaining sauce from pan. Garnish with scallion greens and remaining sesame seeds. Drizzle with @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.